{My Queen’s Gambit Declined is designed to provide you with a complete and
practical repertoire for Black against} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 {. Now,}
4. Nc3 {is the main move. But we will of course also cover all alternatives on
move four — except for the Catalan, against which I have already published a
repertoire on modern-chess.com.} Nbd7 $5 {This system offers a harmonious
balance between activity and solidity, requiring minimal memorization.   What
this course is about:  > 7 Comprehensive Lectures: Covering the entire
Queen’s Gambit Declined repertoire.  > Strategic Clarity: Emphasis on
understanding the key concepts behind each position.  > Practical Focus: A
repertoire that’s simple to learn yet effective at any level.  Lesson 1:
Queen's Gambit Declined - Classical Strategies Lesson 2: Fighting the
Alternatives to 4.Nc3 Lesson 3: White Plays Bf4 without cxd5 Lesson 4: White
Plays Bg5 without cxd5 Lesson 5: Setups with cxd5 and Bf4 - GM Ioannis
Papaioannou Lesson 6: Setups with cxd5 and Bg5 - Part 1  Lesson 7: Setups with
cxd5 and Bg5 - Part 2} *

