{[%evp 0,8,15,30,20,0,0,6,6,6,35] Before diving into the theoretical lines, I
will focus on explaining the key strategic ideas and typical plans that define
the Queen’s Gambit Declined. This approach ensures a deep understanding of
fundamental pawn structures, making it easier to apply the repertoire in your
games.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 $5 {Before going into the
theory, we focus on how to handle some of the most important pawn structures
arising in the QGD. I. Carlsbad structure > exploiting doubled pawns on g2/g3
with ...h5-h4 > transferring the knight to d6 > attacking on the kingside >
two white knights against a black bishop and knight in the middlegame II.
White does not take on d5 > symmetrical position with open c- and d-file >
White plays c4-c5} *

