1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nd7 4. Nc3 Ngf6 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bf4 Nb6 7. e3 {
In this game, we begin to examine positions with two white knights against a
black dark-squared bishop and a knight.} ({Let me create a typical position:} 
7. Qc2 c6 8. e3 Bg4 9. Be2 Be7 10. Ne5 Bxe2 11. Qxe2 O-O 12. O-O Re8 13. Bg5 h6
14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Nf3 (15. Nd3 $2 Bxd4) 15... Be7 {When we have a dark-squared
bishop and a knight, the BISHOP should go to d6!} 16. h3 (16. a3 a5) 16... Nd7
17. Rab1 (17. a3 a5) 17... a5 $1 {In positions with a dark-squared bishop, we
play ...a5 whenever White is ready to play b4. Let's see why:} 18. a3 Bd6 19.
b4 {In order to achieve b4, White had to put his pawns on dark squares so that
they become targets for our bishop!} b5 $1 (19... axb4 20. axb4 b5) 20. Qb2 Qe7
$17 {[%csl Ra3,Rb4][%cal Gd6b4,Gd7b6,Gb6c4]}) 7... Bf5 8. Bd3 Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Bd6
10. Bg5 Be7 11. O-O O-O 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. b4 (13. Rab1 {If White postpones b4,
Black can improve his position with} a5 14. Rfc1 Be7 15. a3 c6 16. Qc2 Bd6 17.
h3 Qe7 (17... Re8)) 13... a6 14. Nd2 Be7 15. Rfb1 c6 16. a4 g6 17. g3 {I call
this position with pawns c6 and a6 and the knight on b6 "Alekseev-setup".
Against this, White has difficulties to carry out b4-b5 in an effective way.} (
{With the knight on b6, the move} 17. b5 {can be met with} cxb5 $1 18. axb5 a5
$1 $15) ({Fixing the queenside with} 17. a5 {is not in White's interest since
now he will no longer be able to play for a minority attack.} Nd7 18. Nb3 Nf6 {
Let's assume that b4 isn't hanging to show the typical ideas.} (18... Bxb4) 19.
Nc5 Rb8 20. Re1 Bd6 {Black has regrouped harmoniously and is ready for play on
the kingside.}) 17... Re8 18. Ne2 Bd6 19. Kg2 (19. b5 {is again met with} cxb5
20. axb5 a5) 19... Qe7 20. Qc3 h5 $15 {Black starts to exploit the weaknesses
created by g3.} 21. Nc1 Nd7 22. Nd3 (22. b5 c5 $5 $17 (22... cxb5 23. axb5 a5
$1 24. Rxa5 Bb4 $1 $17) 23. dxc5 $2 Be5 $19) 22... Nf6 23. Re1 h4 $17 24. f3
hxg3 25. h3 $6 (25. hxg3 Qc7 26. Nf1 Re7 $17 {[%cal Ga8e8]}) 25... Nh5 $19 26.
e4 Bf4 27. Nb3 Qg5 28. Re2 Re7 29. Rae1 Rae8 30. Qb2 Qh4 31. Nbc5 Nf6 32. Nxf4
Qxf4 33. e5 Nh5 34. Qd2 Qh4 35. Re4 dxe4 36. Rxe4 Rxe5 37. dxe5 Rd8 38. Qe3 Qe7
39. e6 Qf6 40. e7 Qb2+ 41. Qe2 Qxe2+ 0-1

