1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 Be7 7. e3 O-O {
Not exchanging on d5 has pros and cons. On the one hand, Black's bishop
remains passive on c8, while Black has pawn breaks available.} 8. Bd3 $6 (8.
cxd5 exd5 {leads to the Carlsbad structure.}) 8... dxc4 $1 9. Bxc4 a6 $5 {
Black already has a good game. White has lost a tempo by first playing Bd3 and
then taking on c4.} 10. O-O ({If} 10. a4 {then either} c5 ({or} 10... b6 11.
O-O Bb7)) 10... b5 11. Bd3 Bb7 12. Qc2 $6 {It is not a good idea to put the
queen on the open c-file.} (12. Qe2 c5 13. dxc5 Nxc5 14. Bc2 Qb6 $15) 12... c5
13. dxc5 Nxc5 14. Be2 Qb6 15. a3 Rfc8 {White's queen is badly placed, while
Black's queen has found a perfect square on b6.} 16. Rfd1 Nce4 $17 {White will
get a backward pawn on the c-file.} 17. Nd4 Rc5 18. Qb3 Nxc3 19. bxc3 Bd5 20.
Qb2 Qc7 21. a4 bxa4 22. Rxa4 a5 23. Bg3 Qc8 24. Qa1 Ne4 25. Nb5 Bf6 26. Rxa5
Rxa5 27. Qxa5 Nxc3 28. Re1 Nxe2+ 29. Rxe2 Rxb5 30. Qxb5 Qc1+ 31. Re1 Qxe1+ 32.
Qf1 Qxf1+ 33. Kxf1 e5 34. f3 e4 35. f4 Bc4+ 36. Kf2 g6 37. h3 Kg7 38. Bh2 Bc3
39. g4 f6 40. Kg3 f5 41. Bg1 Be1+ 42. Kg2 Be2 43. gxf5 gxf5 44. Kh2 Kg6 45. Kg2
Kf6 46. Kh2 Ke6 47. Kg2 h5 48. Kh2 Kd5 49. Kg2 Kc4 50. Kh2 Kd3 51. Kg2 h4 52.
Kh2 Bg3+ 53. Kg2 Kd2 0-1

