c6 {Caruana avoids the symmetrical positions that can arise after 8...c5 and
instead goes for a different plan. With 8...c6, Black is preparing ...dxc4,
followed by ...b5, ...Bb7, etc.} 9. Bd3 a6 10. O-O dxc4 11. Bxc4 b5 12. Bd3 c5
13. Ne4 $6 {This offers interesting chances for Black.} c4 $1 14. Bb1 Bb7 15.
Nxf6+ Nxf6 16. Re1 Ne4 17. Bxe7 Qxe7 $15 {Black is better due to his majority
on the queenside.} 18. b3 cxb3 19. Qxb3 Rfc8 20. Bd3 b4 $1 $17 {Creating a
strong outpost on c3.} 21. Ne5 a5 22. Nc4 Nc3 23. a3 $2 Bd5 $19 24. e4 Bxc4 25.
Bxc4 a4 26. Qb2 Rxc4 27. axb4 Rac8 28. Rc2 Qxb4 29. Qxb4 Rxb4 30. d5 a3 31. d6
