1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Bg5 dxc4 5. Qa4+ Nbd7 6. Bxf6 {This was
probably over-the-board inspiration. However, giving up the bishop for free is
a dubious decision, giving Black some advantage.} (6. e4 Be7 {threatening ...
Nxe4.}) (6. e3 a6 {with the idea ...b5, ...Bb7.}) (6. Qxc4 c5 {followed by ...
a6, ...b5, etc.}) 6... Qxf6 7. Qxc4 Bd6 {A good move, though 7...e5 was more
energetic.} (7... c5 $15) (7... e5 $1 8. dxe5 Nxe5 9. Qb5+ {This is relatively
best. After} (9. Qxc7 {Neglecting the development will lead to problems.} Nxf3+
10. exf3 Bb4+ 11. Nc3 O-O $17) 9... Nd7 $15 {Black keeps an advantage due to
his pair of bishops.}) 8. Nc3 O-O 9. g3 (9. Ne4 Qe7 10. Nxd6 cxd6 {...e5 will
come with a good game for Black.}) 9... e5 10. Ne4 (10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Qxe5
12. Bg2 c6 13. O-O Be6 $17 {[%csl Gd6,Ge6]}) 10... Qe7 11. Nxd6 cxd6 12. Bg2
Nb6 $1 {12...e4 was also strong.} 13. Qc2 e4 14. Nd2 d5 15. Qb3 Bg4 {White is
in big trouble.} 16. h3 Bh5 17. g4 Bg6 18. O-O f5 $17 {White managed to castle
but now Black will exploit the weaknesses created by g4.} 19. gxf5 Bxf5 20.
Rac1 Rf6 21. Rc3 Rg6 22. Rd1 Bd7 23. Qc2 Qh4 24. Nf1 Bxh3 25. Ng3 Rf8 26. b3
Rh6 27. Bh1 Bg4 28. Bg2 Qh2+ 29. Kf1 Bh3 0-1

