transpostion we are back in our repertoire - as we already know, Black has a
good game since White loses too much time with his queen.} h6 {I would prefer
6...c5, but there is nothing wrong with this 6...h6.} 7. Bh4 Be7 8. e3 a6 9. a4
c5 10. a5 {White fights against ...b5, but loses too much time in the process.}
cxd4 11. exd4 Nd5 (11... b5 $1 {I like this even better!} 12. axb6 Qxb6 $17)
12. Bxe7 Qxe7 $15 13. Nc3 N7f6 14. Ne5 O-O 15. Be2 Bd7 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 {Black
has a pleasant position. White has an Isolated Queen's Pawn but no attack.} 17.
Qc5 Rfd8 18. O-O Be8 19. Rfd1 Rac8 20. Qxe7 Nxe7 {Black has a clear and
long-term advantage in this endgame.} 21. Bf3 f6 22. Nd3 Rxd4 23. Bxb7 Rcd8 24.
Bxa6 R8d6 25. Bb7 Rxd3 26. Rxd3 Rxd3 27. h3 Bc6 28. a6 Rd6 $4 (28... Rd7 $19)
29. Bxc6 Nxc6 30. Rc1 $4 (30. a7 $11) 30... Na7 {0-1 (30) Seslija,Z (2110)
-Nikolic,P (2536) Neum 2022} 0-1

