1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. Bf4 Bb4 6. Qa4 $6 Bxc3+ $5 7. bxc3
O-O 8. e3 {In general, if Black manages to play ...c5 in this structure, he is
doing well.} (8. cxd5 exd5 9. e3 c5 $1 10. Bd6 $6 (10. dxc5 Nxc5 $132) (10. Be2
c4 {followed by ...Ne4, ...Ndf6.}) 10... Nb6 11. Qa5 (11. Qa3 $2 Qxd6 12. dxc5
Qe7 $19) 11... Qxd6 12. dxc5 Qc7 13. cxb6 axb6 $1 $15 (13... Qxb6 $11)) 8... c5
9. Qc2 (9. Bd6 Nb6 10. Qa5 (10. Qa3 Qxd6 $19) 10... Qxd6 11. dxc5 Qc7 12. cxb6
Qxb6 13. Qxb6 axb6 $15) 9... Qa5 $1 {My idea was follow up with ...b6, ...Ba6.}
(9... b6 10. cxd5 (10. Bd3 Ba6 $132) 10... exd5 11. Bd3 a5 12. O-O Ba6 $14) 10.
Nd2 b6 $6 (10... cxd4 $1 {was the more precise way to execute Black's plan.}
11. cxd4 b6 $132) 11. Bd3 (11. a4 $1 cxd4 12. exd4 $14) 11... Ba6 $15 12. a4 ({
After} 12. Nb3 {Black has} Qa4) 12... cxd4 13. exd4 (13. Bd6 $2 Qxc3 $19) 13...
dxc4 14. Bxc4 Bxc4 (14... Nd5 15. Nb3 Bxc4 16. Nxa5 bxa5) 15. Nxc4 Qh5 $3 (
15... Qd5 16. Ne3 Qh5 17. c4 e5 18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Bxe5 Qxe5 20. O-O $11 {/=/+})
16. Ne5 (16. O-O Nd5 $1 17. Bg3 (17. Bd2 Rfc8) 17... Rfc8 $15) 16... Nxe5 $1 (
16... Nd5 $5 17. Nxd7 Nxf4 18. Nxf8 Nxg2+ 19. Kf1 Qf3 $3 $15) 17. Bxe5 Nd7 18.
Bg3 Qd5 $1 $17 {I saw that I can get c4 under control - with a large advantage
for Black.} 19. O-O (19. c4 {does not work.} Qxg2 20. O-O-O Rac8 $19) 19...
Rfc8 20. Qb2 Qc4 (20... Rc4 $5) 21. Rfc1 Nf6 22. Bf4 Nd5 23. Bd2 h6 $6 (23...
Qe2 $1 $17) 24. Qb5 Rc7 25. Qxc4 Rxc4 26. Kf1 Rac8 27. Ra3 (27. Ke2 Nxc3+ 28.
Kd3 Nxa4 29. Rxa4 Rxc1 30. Bxc1 Rxc1 31. Rxa7 Rh1 32. Ke3 Rxh2 33. g3 Rh5 34.
Rb7 Rb5 $19) 27... Ne7 $1 (27... f6 28. Ke2 Kf7 29. Kd3 g5 $15) 28. Ke2 Nc6 29.
Rb1 (29. Kd3 Nxd4 30. cxd4 Rxc1 31. Bxc1 Rxc1 32. a5 bxa5 33. Rxa5 Rh1 34. Ke3
Rxh2 35. g3 Rh1 (35... a6) 36. Rxa7 Rh5) 29... Na5 30. Ra2 R4c6 (30... e5 $3
$17) 31. Be1 g5 32. Kd3 Kh7 33. f3 Kg6 34. Rb5 f6 35. Re2 Nc4 36. Ra2 h5 37.
Rb1 h4 38. Rb4 e5 39. Rb1 f5 40. Rb4 e4+ $3 $17 41. fxe4 fxe4+ 42. Ke2 (42.
Kxe4 Re6+ 43. Kd5 Rcc6 44. Bf2 (44. Rxc4 Rcd6#) (44. Re2 Rcd6+ 45. Kxc4 Rxe2
$19) 44... Na5 45. Rd2 Rcd6#) 42... a6 (42... Rf6 $3 $19 43. Ra1 a5 $3 44. Rb5
Rcf8 45. Rab1 Rf1 46. Rd5 Rg1 $19) 43. Ra1 Rd8 44. Rab1 Kf5 45. Bf2 Rd5 46. Rf1
Ke6 47. Be3 Rc8 $1 48. Bc1 Rf5 49. Rxf5 Kxf5 $17 50. d5 g4 $5 (50... Rc5 $1 51.
d6 Nxd6 52. Rxb6 Rxc3 53. Rxd6 $2 Rxc1 54. Rxa6 Rc2+ 55. Kf1 Ra2 $19) 51. d6
Ke6 (51... Nxd6 52. Rxb6 Rxc3 53. Bd2 (53. Rxd6 Rxc1 54. Rxa6 Rh1 $15) 53...
Nc4 $1 $17) 52. Be3 a5 $2 {Not the best, but White was already down to his
last seconds for many moves now ...} (52... Rc6 $1 $17) 53. Rb1 Nxe3 (53...
Kxd6 54. Bxb6) 54. Kxe3 Rxc3+ 55. Kf4 (55. Kxe4) 55... Rc2 (55... e3 $1) 56.
Rd1 $2 (56. Kxg4 Rxg2+ 57. Kxh4 Kxd6 $3 58. Rxb6+ Kd5 59. Rb5+ Kd4 60. Rxa5 e3
61. Ra8 e2 62. Re8 Kd3 63. a5 Rxh2+ (63... Kd2) 64. Kg3 Rh1) 56... Kd7 $19 57.
Ke5 e3 58. Rf1 e2 59. Rf7+ Kc8 60. Rf8+ Kb7 0-1

