{A perfect game by the player with the black pieces!} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3
Nf6 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. e3 {Against lines with e3, we can go for the universal
setup: ...b6, ...Bb7, ...Bd6, ...0-0, ...Nbd7. However, there are some
move-order subtleties.} a6 $1 {This is best in this specific move order.} (5...
b6 $6 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bb5 Bb7 8. Ne5) 6. b3 (6. cxd5 exd5 {[%csl Rc1] leads to
a good version (for Black) of the Carlsbad structure.}) (6. Be2 dxc4 $1 7. Bxc4
b5 8. Bd3 c5 9. O-O Bb7 {leads to a Queen's Gambit Accepted with an extra
tempo for Black. Since also the misplaced knight on c3 is often misplaced,
Black is better.}) (6. c5 $6 b6 $1 7. c6 (7. b4 a5 $1 8. c6 axb4 $3 9. cxd7+
Bxd7 10. Nb1 c5 $17 {Black has more than enough compensation for the piece.})
7... Nb8 8. Ne5 Qd6 9. Qa4 Ne4 $1 10. Nxe4 dxe4 $17 {...f6 is coming and White
will lose c6.}) 6... b6 $1 {Only now we go for the universal setup.} 7. Bd3 ({
If White plays} 7. Bb2 Bb7 8. Be2 {we can follow the same strategy as in the
game.} ({White can also go for a fianchetto with} 8. cxd5 exd5 9. g3 {Here, we
can potentially go for castling queenside!} Bd6 10. Bg2 Qe7 {[%cal Ge8c8]})
8... Bd6 9. O-O O-O 10. Rc1 dxc4 (10... Qe7) 11. bxc4 (11. Bxc4 $6 b5 12. Be2
c5 $15) 11... c5 12. d5 exd5 13. Nxd5 Bxd5 14. cxd5 b5 $1 $132 (14... Re8 $2
15. a4 $1 $16)) 7... Bb7 8. O-O Bd6 9. Bb2 O-O 10. Qe2 dxc4 11. bxc4 (11. Bxc4
b5 12. Bd3 c5 13. dxc5 Nxc5 $17) 11... c5 12. Rfd1 ({If} 12. d5 {then} exd5 13.
Nxd5 Bxd5 $1 14. cxd5 b5 (14... Nxd5 $2 15. Bxh7+ $1) 15. e4 Re8 $132) 12...
cxd4 13. exd4 Qc7 14. h3 Rfe8 15. Ng5 Bf8 16. Qc2 g6 {Black has a good game.} (
16... h6 $4 17. Bh7+ Kh8 18. Nxf7#) 17. Nge4 Bg7 18. Ba3 Nxe4 19. Bxe4 Nf6 20.
Bxb7 Qxb7 21. Rab1 Qc6 22. Qb3 Rec8 23. c5 bxc5 24. dxc5 Bf8 25. Rdc1 Nd7 26.
Na4 Rab8 27. Qc2 Rb5 28. Rxb5 axb5 29. Nb2 Qa6 30. Qb3 Bxc5 31. Bxc5 Rxc5 32.
Rd1 Qc6 33. Nd3 Rd5 34. Rc1 Qd6 35. Nb4 Rd2 36. a3 Qd4 37. Qf3 Kg7 38. Rc7 Ne5
39. Qg3 h5 40. Rb7 h4 41. Qe3 Qd6 42. Qc3 Rd1+ 43. Kh2 Kh7 44. g3 hxg3+ 45.
Qxg3 Nf3+ 46. Kg2 Rg1+ 47. Kxf3 Rxg3+ 48. fxg3 Qd1+ 0-1

