1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 Be7 7. e3 O-O 8. Bd3
(8. Rc1 c5 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Bxe7 Nxe7 $1 ({We avoid the positions with an
isolated pawn after} 10... Qxe7 11. Nxd5 exd5 12. dxc5 Nxc5 13. Be2 $14) 11.
dxc5 (11. Be2 b6 $1 (11... cxd4 {is also possible, but perhaps slightly less
accurate. For example} 12. Nxd4 Nf6 13. O-O Bd7 14. Bf3 Qb6 15. Qb3 Qxb3 16.
Nxb3 Rab8 {with good equalising chances.}) 12. O-O Bb7 13. Qc2 (13. dxc5 Nxc5
14. Qxd8 Rfxd8 {Black has fully equalised; the line can continue with} 15. Rfd1
Nd5 {If White is not careful, he can easily land in a slightly worse position:}
16. Nxd5 Bxd5 17. b3 (17. a3 Nb3 18. Rc3 Rac8 19. Rxc8 Rxc8 $15) 17... Bxf3 $1
{I like this concept! White's bishop has no targets at all while Black can
manoeuvre with his knight.} 18. Bxf3 Rxd1+ 19. Rxd1 Rc8 20. Kf1 (20. b4 Na4)
20... Kf8 21. Rc1 a5 22. Ke2 Ke7 23. Rc2 g5 24. h3 Rc7 25. Rc4 b5 26. Rc2 b4
27. Rc4 f5 28. Rc2 (28. Kd2 Ne4+ 29. Bxe4 Rxc4 $19) 28... Kd6 29. Kd2 e5 30. g3
e4 31. Be2 Nd7 32. Rxc7 Kxc7 $17) 13... Rc8 14. Rfd1 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Nd5 {
Black has a good game. For example} 16. Qd2 Nxc3 17. Rxc3 Nf6 (17... Rxc3 18.
Qxc3 $14) 18. Rxc8 Qxc8 19. Rc1 Qd7 $11) 11... Nxc5 12. Qc2 Bd7 {This is a
playable alternative to 12...b6.} (12... b6 $1) 13. Be2 (13. Ne5 Rc8) 13... Rc8
14. Ne5 Qb6 $5 {Typically, we welcome the exchange of a white knight against
our light-squared bishop since White's bishop tends to be impotent in the
resulting position.} 15. Nxd7 Nxd7 16. O-O Nf6 17. Bf3 Rfd8 {It's about equal,
but I would prefer Black.}) (8. Qc2 c5 9. cxd5 (9. O-O-O a6 $15 (9... b6 $15) (
9... cxd4 $15) 10. cxd5 Nxd5 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 $3 $17) 9... Nxd5 {A possible
alternative to 9...cxd4.} (9... cxd4 $1 10. Nxd4 Nxd5 11. Bxe7 Nxe7 {- see
THEORY.}) 10. Bxe7 (10. Nxd5 $2 Bxh4 $17 11. Nc3 (11. Nxh4 $6 exd5 (11... Qxh4
$5 $15) 12. Nf3 c4 $15) 11... cxd4 12. Nxd4 Qb6 13. Be2 Bf6 14. Rd1 Nc5 15. O-O
Bd7 $15) 10... Nxe7 $1 11. dxc5 (11. O-O-O $2 {This almost never works for
White in these lines.} Qa5 $15 12. Kb1 cxd4 13. Nxd4 Nf6 14. Nb3 (14. Be2 e5
15. Nb3 Qb6 $15) 14... Qc7 15. Be2 Bd7 $15) (11. Be2 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Nf6 13. O-O
(13. O-O-O Bd7 $15 14. Bf3 Qa5 (14... Rc8 $17) (14... Rb8 $17)) 13... Bd7 14.
Rfd1 Qb6 15. Rac1 Rac8 $132) 11... Qa5 $1 12. Be2 Qxc5 13. O-O Nf6 14. Rac1 Bd7
15. Rfd1 Qa5 $132 {Black has a good game. Let's continue with some sample
lines:} 16. Qb3 Rab8 17. Nd4 (17. h3 Rfd8 $11 (17... b5 $2 18. Ne5 $16)) 17...
Rfd8 $11 (17... e5 $6 18. Ndb5 $14) (17... a6 $5 18. Bf3 $140 e5 $1 19. Nde2
Be6 $15)) 8... dxc4 $1 {This is Black's most logical reaction after 8.Bd3.} (
8... c5 $5 {is a playable alternative.} 9. cxd5 (9. dxc5 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Nxc5 $11
) 9... Nxd5 $1 10. Bxe7 Nxe7 11. O-O cxd4 (11... b6 12. Be4 Rb8 13. Qe2 cxd4
14. Nxd4 Nc5 15. Bf3 Ba6 $36) 12. Nxd4 Nf6 13. Rc1 Qb6 (13... Bd7 $11) 14. Qb3
Qxb3 15. Nxb3 b6 16. Rfd1 Bb7 $11) 9. Bxc4 c5 $1 (9... a6 $1 {with the idea of
playing ...b5 and provoking White to weaken himself with a4.} 10. a4 b6 (10...
c5)) 10. dxc5 $6 (10. O-O cxd4 11. Nxd4 Qb6 $1 (11... Nb6 $1 12. Be2 (12. Bd3
$6 Nfd5 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. Nxd5 Nxd5 15. Rc1 Rd8 16. Qe2 e5 17. Nf5 Bxf5 18.
Bxf5 g6 19. Be4 Nf6 $132) 12... Nfd5 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. Nxd5 Nxd5 15. Bf3 Nf6
16. Nb3 (16. Qb3) 16... Rb8 17. Rc1 b6 18. Qc2 e5 19. Be2 (19. Qc7 Qxc7 20.
Rxc7 a5 $15) 19... Be6 20. h3 Rfc8 21. Qb1 Qb4 $15) 12. Qe2 (12. Bb3 Nc5) 12...
Ne5 13. Bb3 Bd7 {Black is about to bring his rooks into play with ...Rfd8 and .
..Rac8 and has a good position. For example} 14. Bg3 Nc6 15. Rfd1 ({Black is
slightly better after} 15. Nxc6 $6 Bxc6 $15 {[%csl Gc6] with a possible
continuation being:} 16. Rfd1 Rfd8 17. h3 Qa5 18. Rac1 (18. a3 Qg5) 18... Rac8
19. Rxd8+ Rxd8 20. Rd1 Rxd1+ 21. Qxd1 a6 22. Qe2 Qg5 $15) 15... a6 16. Rac1
Rac8 {Black is doing fine. Let's see some ideas:} 17. h3 Nxd4 (17... Rfd8 $132)
18. Rxd4 Bc6 $15 19. Bd6 Bxd6 20. Rxd6 Rfd8 21. Rcd1 Rxd6 22. Rxd6 Qc5 23. Rd2
(23. Qd2 $4 Bd5 $19) 23... g6 $1 $15 (23... Qg5 24. f3 b5 $15) 24. a3 Kg7 $15
25. Qd1 Qg5 $17 (25... b5)) 10... Nxc5 11. Qxd8 $2 Rxd8 $15 12. O-O Bd7 $1 (
12... a6 $1 13. Rfd1 (13. a4 Bd7 $15 14. Rfd1 (14. a5 Rac8 15. Be2 Nb3 $1 (
15... g5 16. Bg3 Nfe4 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 $17 18. Be5 $2 g4 19. Nd4 f6 20. Bg3 e5 21.
Nb3 Be6 22. Nc1 Rd2 $19) 16. Ra2 Bb4 17. Ne5 Be8 $19) 14... Rac8 15. Be2 g5 16.
Bg3 Nfe4 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 18. Nd4 Nxg3 19. hxg3 Rc7 20. Rac1 Rdc8 21. Rxc7 Rxc7
$17) (13. Ne5 g5 14. Bg3 Nce4 15. Nxe4 Nxe4 16. Rfd1 b5 $1 $15 (16... Nxg3 17.
hxg3 Rxd1+ 18. Rxd1 Kg7 (18... b5 19. Be2 $11) 19. Nd7 b5 20. Nb6 Rb8 21. Nxc8
Rxc8 $15) 17. Bd3 Bb7 $15) 13... b5 14. Rxd8+ Bxd8 15. Be2 Bb7 16. Rd1 b4 17.
Nb1 Bd5 18. b3 g5 19. Bg3 Nfe4 $19) 13. Rfd1 (13. Ne5 $2 g5 $17 (13... Be8 $17
14. Rfd1 g5 15. Bg3 Nce4) 14. Nxd7 Rxd7 15. Bg3 Nce4 $1 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Be5
Bf6 $1 18. Bxf6 Nxf6 19. Rfd1 Rc8 $3 $15 20. Rxd7 Nxd7 21. Bb3 Kf8 22. Kf1 Ke7
23. Ke2 a5 $17) 13... Rac8 14. Be2 g5 15. Bg3 Nfe4 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Rac1 Nxg3
18. hxg3 Rxc1 19. Rxc1 Bf6 $17 20. b3 Rc8 (20... Bc6) 21. Rxc8+ Bxc8 22. Nd2
Kf8 23. Ne4 Be7 24. Kf1 g4 $3 $17 *

