12. Nxd4 Nf6 13. O-O a6 14. Be2 Bd7 15. Bf3 e5 {This is a common idea here,
though, in general, we should be careful when playing ...e5 since some
weaknesses on the light-squares are created.} ({A solid alternative is} 15...
Rb8 16. Ne4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 e5 18. Nf3 Bc6 19. Bxc6 Nxc6 $11 {The game is equal,
but there is still some play left:} 20. Qe2 $2 e4 (20... Qe7) 21. Nd2 f5 22.
Rfd1 Qe7 23. Nb3 Ne5 $15) 16. Nb3 Qb6 {The queen is safe on b6 - Black has a
fully satisfactory game.} 17. Ne4 Bb5 18. Re1 Rfd8 19. Qc2 Rac8 20. Qb1 Bd3 $1
$15 21. Nxf6+ gxf6 22. Qa1 Bc2 23. h3 Rc7 $6 (23... f5 $15) (23... Qb4 $3 $17)
24. Bd1 $11 {/+/=} Be4 25. Rxc7 Qxc7 26. Bh5 Kh7 27. Qc1 Qxc1 28. Rxc1 Kg7 29.
