1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 Be7 7. e3 O-O 8. Rc1
c5 9. cxd5 ({If} 9. Be2 {Black has a choice between two good moves:} cxd4 $1 (
9... dxc4 $1 10. Bxc4 a6 11. a4 (11. O-O $2 b5 12. Be2 Bb7 $15) 11... cxd4 12.
Nxd4 Qb6 13. Qe2 Ne5 14. Ba2 Bd7 15. O-O Rac8 $15 16. Rfd1 Rfd8 17. Bb1 Qb4 18.
Bg3 Nc6 $17 19. Nf3 Nh5 $17 (19... Be8 $17)) 10. exd4 dxc4 11. Bxc4 Nb6 {
Black has a good version of a position with an IQP. A typical idea can be seen
after} (11... b6 {is playable, though I don't like the fact that after} 12. O-O
Bb7 {the knight on d7 may be left "unemployed".}) 12. Bb3 Bd7 (12... Nfd5) 13.
Ne5 Bc6 {- even this is very playble for Black.} 14. Nxc6 bxc6 $11 {[%csl Gd5]}
) 9... Nxd5 10. Bxe7 Nxe7 11. Bd3 cxd4 $1 $132 (11... b6 $1 $132) 12. exd4 $2 {
A terrible move - White accepts an isolated pawn, but without any realistic
attacking chances!} Nf6 13. O-O Bd7 $1 $15 14. Bb1 (14. Ne5 Bc6 $15) 14... Bc6
15. Qd3 (15. Re1 Ned5 {Let me highlight one idea:} 16. h3 {Black may at any
point turn the IQP position into one with Hanging Pawns:} Nxc3 $1 (16... Nf4 $1
$15) 17. bxc3 Bxf3 $3 18. Qxf3 {With limited material on the board, Black has
good chances against the Hanging Pawns. For example} b5 $15 (18... b6 19. Red1
Rc8 20. c4 Qd6 21. Qe3 Rfd8 $15) (18... Rb8 19. Qe2 Qc7 20. Red1 b5 $15 (20...
Rfd8))) 15... Qb6 $1 16. Ne5 Rfd8 (16... Qxb2 $4 17. Nc4 $18) 17. Rfd1 (17. Ng4
$2 Nxg4 18. Qh7+ Kf8 19. Qh8+ Ng8 $19) 17... Rac8 $1 18. Qe3 $2 (18. Qd2 $15)
18... Qxb2 $1 $19 19. Re1 Ned5 20. Qg3 Nxc3 21. Rxc3 Bd5 22. Rce3 Rc1 $1 23.
Nd3 Rxe1+ 24. Rxe1 Qxd4 25. Qc7 Be4 26. Rd1 Qd7 27. Qc1 Qc6 28. Qe3 Bxg2 29.
Rc1 Qf3 30. Qe5 Qg4 31. Qc7 Be4+ 0-1

