{An amazing and nearly flawless game by Black - Congratulations!} 1. d4 Nf6 2.
Nf3 e6 3. c4 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. cxd5 (5. Qc2 c5 6. cxd5 Nxd5 $3 7. Nxd5 exd5 8.
dxc5 Nxc5 $132) 5... exd5 6. Bf4 Nb6 7. e3 Bf5 8. Ne5 Bd6 9. Be2 h6 $5 (9...
O-O $1 10. g4 ({If White plays} 10. O-O {we get a comfortable position after
for example} c6 11. Rc1 h6) 10... Be6 11. h4 (11. Qc2 Rc8 $3 $15 {[%cal Gc7c5]}
12. g5 (12. O-O-O $2 c5 $17) 12... Ne4 $1 13. Nxe4 dxe4 $17) 11... Ne4 $3 {
If White plays g4, we usually answer with ...Be6, followed by ...Ne4 - see the
game!} 12. Nxe4 $2 (12. Qc2 Nxc3 (12... Rc8) 13. bxc3) 12... dxe4 $17 13. g5 f6
14. gxf6 Qxf6 $17 15. Bg3 Rad8 16. Qc2 c5 (16... Bb4+ 17. Kf1 c5)) 10. g4 Be6
11. Bg3 Ne4 $3 {REMEMBER THE RULE! If White plays an early g2-g4, it is
usually very good for Black to go for ...Ne4!} 12. Nxe4 dxe4 $15 13. O-O O-O
14. Qc2 Bd5 15. Nc4 $2 Nxc4 $1 16. Bxc4 Bxc4 $1 17. Qxc4 Qg5 $1 $17 {By now
it's clear that White's risky strategy has backfired.} 18. Qe2 f5 $3 19. gxf5
Rxf5 20. Kh1 Raf8 21. Rg1 Qf6 22. Qg4 Qe7 23. Bh4 g5 $3 24. Rg2 Kh7 25. Bg3
Bxg3 26. Qxg3 Rf3 27. Qe5 Qxe5 28. dxe5 Re8 (28... Rxf2 $1 $19) 29. Rd1 Kg6 30.
Rd7 Rf7 31. Rxf7 Kxf7 32. Rg1 Rxe5 $17 33. Rd1 Ke7 34. Kg2 c5 35. Kg3 Rf5 36.
Rd2 h5 37. a4 b6 38. b3 a6 39. h3 b5 40. axb5 axb5 41. Ra2 Kd6 42. Ra8 c4 43.
b4 Rf7 44. Ra6+ Kd5 45. Rb6 c3 46. Rxb5+ Kc4 47. Rxg5 Kxb4 48. Kh4 c2 49. Rg1
Rxf2 50. Kxh5 Kc3 51. Kg4 Kd2 52. h4 c1=Q 53. Rxc1 Kxc1 54. h5 Kd2 0-1

