1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 c6 4. Nc3 e6 5. Bg5 Nbd7 6. cxd5 exd5 7. e3 h6 8. Bh4
Be7 9. Bd3 Ne4 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. Qc2 Ndf6 12. Ne5 Bf5 $4 {A losing mistake! Be
aware of the following trick!} 13. O-O $4 {White misses his chance!} (13. Nxc6
$3 bxc6 14. Nxe4 Qb4+ 15. Nd2 Bxd3 16. Qxd3 Qxb2 17. O-O $18) 13... O-O 14. a3
Nxc3 $5 (14... Rfe8 $1 {is a good alternative since White does not threaten f3.
} 15. b4 $2 (15. Ne2 Bh7 16. Nf4 a6 17. Rac1 Nd6 $15) 15... Nxc3 16. Bxf5 Nce4
17. Rab1 g6 18. Bxe4 Nxe4 $15 19. Rfc1 (19. b5 c5 20. f3 Nf6) 19... a6 20. a4
Kg7 $3 $17 {A necessary prophlylaxis!} (20... Nd6 {can be answered with} 21.
Nxg6 fxg6 22. Qxg6+ Kh8 (22... Qg7 $4 23. Qxd6 $18) 23. Qxh6+ Kg8 $11) 21. b5
$2 cxb5 $1 (21... axb5 $3 22. axb5 c5 23. f3 cxd4 24. exd4 Rac8 25. Qd3 Nd6 $17
) 22. axb5 axb5 $15 23. Rxb5 Rec8 $1 24. Qb2 Rxc1+ 25. Qxc1 Qc7 $3 (25... Ra2
$17) 26. Rb1 Nc3 27. Kf1 Qa5 $17) 15. bxc3 {This is the only ambitious try.} (
15. Bxf5 Nce4 $36) (15. Qxc3 Bxd3 16. Qxd3 Ne4 $15) 15... Bxd3 16. Nxd3 Ne4 (
16... Rac8 17. c4 dxc4 18. Qxc4 b6 19. a4 Ne4 20. Rfd1 c5 21. dxc5 Nxc5 $15) (
