1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bh4 Bb4 8.
e3 (8. a3 Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 c5 $132) 8... g5 9. Bg3 Ne4 10. Nd2 Nxg3 11. hxg3 c6 (
11... Nf6 $4 12. Qa4+ $18) 12. Bd3 Nf6 $6 (12... Kf8 $1) 13. Qc2 $6 (13. Nf3 $1
$14) 13... Be6 $6 (13... Kf8 $1) 14. O-O-O $6 (14. Nf3 $1 $14) 14... Qe7 15.
Kb1 O-O-O {White didn't punish Black's inferior move order and as a result,
Black is at least equal.} 16. Nb3 Kb8 17. Na4 Bd6 $15 18. Nac5 Bc8 {Black has
consolidated his position and is ready to start counterplay on the kingside.}
19. Rc1 h5 20. Na5 {White has different tactical ideas, which are however
easily defused.} Qc7 (20... Bxc5 $15 {Black exchanges this annoying knight one
move later. was the simplest way.}) 21. Qa4 Bxc5 22. Rxc5 Nd7 23. Rc3 Nb6 24.
Qa3 Qd6 25. b4 ({Black is happy after the exchange of queens.} 25. Qxd6+ Rxd6
26. Nb3 h4 27. gxh4 Rxh4 28. Rxh4 gxh4 $15) 25... h4 $17 26. gxh4 Rxh4 27. Rhc1
Rh2 28. Qb3 Rxg2 29. b5 {White fails to create real threats with this.} cxb5
30. Qxb5 Rxf2 31. e4 Bd7 32. Qc5 Qh2 33. Rb3 Rc8 34. Qa3 Rxc1+ 35. Qxc1 Rg2 36.
e5 Rg1 37. Bf1 Qf2 0-1

