1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Nc3 Bb4 {This is the Ragozin
Defence, which is not our repertoire. However, the game will soon transpose to
our lines.} (5... c6 $1 {see LESSON 3.}) 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bh4 Nbd7 8. e3 g5 9. Bg3
Ne4 10. Nd2 Nxg3 11. hxg3 c6 12. Bd3 Nf6 13. Qc2 Qe7 14. O-O-O Be6 15. Kb1 (15.
f4 O-O-O 16. Nf3 Kb8 17. Ne5 {How should Black continue?} Ng4 $1 18. Rde1 ({If
} 18. f5 Nxe5 19. dxe5 Bc8 {White loses the e5-pawn.}) 18... Nxe5 {This
exchange is always good for Black, regardless whether White takes back with
the f- or d-pawn.} 19. dxe5 (19. fxe5 f6 (19... h5) 20. exf6 Qxf6 21. Rhf1 Qg7
$17) 19... Bc8 {Black prepares ...f6.} (19... d4 $5 20. exd4 Rxd4 $17) 20. Kb1
f6 $1 21. exf6 Qxf6 22. f5 h5 $17) 15... O-O-O 16. Na4 Kb8 17. Rc1 Nd7 {
Not the best plan.} ({In my opinion} 17... Bd6 $5 {is better; for example} 18.
Nc5 Bc8 19. Ndb3 Ka8 $132 {[%cal Gh6h5,Gh5h4]}) 18. Nb3 Nb6 $6 {I don't like
inviting White's knight to c5.} (18... Rc8 $5 $11) 19. Nac5 $14 Bc8 20. a3 Bxc5
21. Nxc5 Na8 22. b4 Nc7 23. Ka1 Rd6 24. Rb1 b6 25. Rb2 Rf6 26. Rhb1 Nb5 27. Qb3
bxc5 28. bxc5 a6 29. a4 Qb7 30. Qb4 Kc7 31. Qa5+ Kd7 32. axb5 axb5 33. Ra2 Rd8
34. Qb4 1/2-1/2

