1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bh4 Nbd7 8.
e3 g5 9. Bg3 Ne4 10. Nd2 ({If White plays a random move like} 10. Qd3 $2 {
we will either play} h5 $15 {or ...c6 - we figure it out over the board!})
10... Nxg3 11. hxg3 c6 12. Qc2 Nb6 13. Be2 {How should be continue?} Be6 {
This (or maybe ...Qe7) is the right way in connection with 12...Nb6.} 14. O-O-O
({If} 14. a3 {we can choose between} Bf8 ({or} 14... Bd6) 15. O-O-O Bg7 16. Kb1
Qe7 17. Nb3 O-O-O 18. Nc5 Kb8 19. Nxe6 (19. N3a4 Bc8 20. Nxb6 axb6 21. Nd3 Bf5
$17) 19... fxe6 20. f4 {Such a position is horrible for White - we can
continue with} c5 21. Bg4 Nc4 $17) 14... Qf6 $3 {With the knight on b6, we
prepare for queenside castling.} 15. Rhf1 ({After} 15. f4 {we sooner or later
will take advantage of White's weak e-pawn.} O-O-O 16. Nf3 Kb8 17. Ne5 Qg7 (
17... Bd6) 18. a3 Bxc3 19. Qxc3 Nc8 (19... f6 20. Nd3 Nc8 21. Nc5 Rhe8 $17) 20.
Nd3 Nd6 21. Nc5 Bc8 22. Kb1 Rhe8 $17) 15... O-O-O $15 {Black has a very
comfortable position.} 16. Na4 Qe7 {Instead of this, I prefer either 16...Bd6
or 16...Kb8.} (16... Bd6 17. Nc5 Kb8 $15) (16... Kb8 17. Nc5 h5 $15) 17. Nc5
Bxc5 18. Qxc5 Qxc5+ 19. dxc5 Nd7 20. b4 a5 21. a3 Kc7 22. Nb3 axb4 23. axb4 Ra8
24. Kb2 Ra4 25. b5 Rha8 26. Ra1 Rxa1 27. Rxa1 Rxa1 28. Kxa1 d4 29. Nxd4 Nxc5
30. bxc6 bxc6 31. f3 Bd7 32. Kb2 Kd6 33. Kc3 Na4+ 34. Kd2 c5 35. Nc2 Be6 36.
Na3 Nb6 37. Kc3 f5 38. Bd3 h5 39. f4 gxf4 40. gxf4 h4 41. Nb5+ Ke7 42. Kd2 Nc4+
43. Ke2 Nb2 44. Nc3 Nxd3 45. Kxd3 Bd7 46. e4 Bc6 47. e5 Bxg2 48. Ke3 Bc6 49.
Kf2 Kd7 50. Kg1 Bf3 51. Kh2 Bg4 52. Na4 Kc6 53. e6 c4 54. e7 Bh5 55. Kh3 Be8
56. Kxh4 Kd5 57. Nb6+ Kc5 58. Nxc4 1/2-1/2

